# ADR-NNNN — {{Title}}

> **Save this file at:** `docs/adr/NNNN-{{kebab-case-slug}}.md` (e.g. `docs/adr/0007-use-postgres-for-write-model.md`)
> **Numbering:** monotonic, never reused. New ADRs get the next number even if an old one is superseded.

## When to write an ADR (the 3-test threshold)

Write an ADR **only if all three are true**:

1. **Hard to reverse** — the cost of changing your mind later is meaningful.
2. **Surprising without context** — a future reader will wonder "why did they do it this way?"
3. **Result of a real trade-off** — there were genuine alternatives and you picked one for specific reasons.

If any of the three is missing, don't write an ADR. Just do the work. (Source: mattpocock/skills `grill-with-docs`.)

---

## Context

What problem are we solving? What constraints apply? Reference [[CONTEXT.md]] terms and any earlier ADRs that informed this.

Keep this to one paragraph if possible. If it's longer, your context might actually be code-or-test-able evidence — capture that separately.

## Decision

What we are doing. Be specific. State the decision in one sentence at the top, then expand.

## Alternatives considered

For each alternative we seriously evaluated:

- **{{Alternative A}}** — Why it was considered. Why it was rejected.
- **{{Alternative B}}** — Why it was considered. Why it was rejected.

If you didn't seriously evaluate alternatives, this decision probably doesn't meet the 3-test threshold above — reconsider whether you need an ADR at all.

## Consequences

- **Positive:** what this enables / fixes / simplifies.
- **Negative:** what this costs / locks us into / makes harder.
- **Risks we are accepting:** known unknowns and how we'd notice if they become problems.

## Related

- [[CONTEXT.md]] — terms touched by this decision.
- [[ADR-MMMM]] — prior decision this builds on or supersedes.
- [[docs/architecture/...]] — diagrams or specs this decision drives.

---

## After acceptance

When this ADR is accepted:

1. Update `docs/adr/INDEX.md` with a one-line summary.
2. If this ADR **supersedes** an earlier one, edit the earlier one's `status` to `Superseded by [[ADR-NNNN]]`. Don't delete it.
3. If this ADR introduces or renames a term, update [[CONTEXT.md]].
4. Reference this ADR in any code comment that depends on the decision (e.g. `// See ADR-0007`).
